		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">majorspawn wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />ok thank you. I am hoping that you speak on behalf of yourself as others might be willing to go a bit further. Also I'm not sure why your treating this question as a &quot;trade secret&quot; I obviously can use a 2A3B/3M board etc. I have however a few BA3M boards which I would hate to waste so I want to make best use of these if possible.</div><br /><br />It isn't a &quot;trade secret&quot;. But this kind of question has been beaten to death on here. If you search this forum you'll find numerous other people who made accounts simply to learn how to make repros/bootlegs, and then vanish. Don't take it personally, but people here for the most part are tired of the &quot;I have no experience, please tell me how to make this $$$ game work&quot;. If you do a bit of research, videos/tutorials of people showcasing how to make repros are everywhere. Just look over at the racketboy forum to find a bunch of info there.<br /><br />If you want to learn, then research. Practice. Experiment.<br /><br />Alternatively, there are people who make and sell boards so that donor carts are not needed at all: <a href="http://www.infiniteneslives.com" class="postlink">http://www.infiniteneslives.com</a> or <a href="http://www.retrostage.net" class="postlink">http://www.retrostage.net</a>

		

