	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Basically what you need is a demux, just like <a href="http://www.play-hookey.com/digital/combinational/decoder_demux_two.html" class="postlink">this one.</a> <br />It will enable or disable the memory chips according to the address on the input.<br />If you have a MAD chip onboard you probably already have it.<br />Just think a little. the information that was give here is enough, you just need to look at it carefully.<br />If you have some more doubts about the circuit I'm sure people here can help.<br /><br />Sincerelly, I think combinational logic should be teached at school.<br />It took me a long time to (kind of) learn it... the teachers on the technician course didn't know it very well. Damm!! Even hexadecimal numbering was considered a thing of another world!!<br />I ended learning the basics of it at university, on the architecture &quot;chair&quot; (I don't know how the parts of a university course are called, so I'm using the word &quot;chair&quot; that is what it's called here...).<br />I ended up learning a lot more here in the forums. But still there's a huge amount of things i need/want to learn!<br /><br />Good luck!

		

		</td>
